            "body": "I used the nightly version\n\n```\n# sshed to server\n❯ ./nvim-linux64/bin/nvim -v\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1589+g71507281fb\n```\n\n\n### server + client `1000000` baud\n\nCrash still happens:\n```\nfish: Job 1, './nvim-linux64/bin/nvim' terminated by signal SIGSEGV (Address boundary error)\n                                                                                            ⏎           ~\n❯ !+`4 7#=5^C\n\n~\n❯ 055 35# 3 257 #! 57#3 257 # 257#5^C\n\n~\n❯ 3 3 37XZ8 ; 4;!7\n```\n\n### Mismatched baud rate\n\nnvim now works as normal. I was able to load up a file and view it, which I could not do before due to the freezing",
